author: @BiancaAguglia
text: Great advice as usual, Krish.  One extra tip that works here, in the US, is to go to local meetups. The meetups for data science and Python are a good start, but there are also many meetups for local businesses. They give you chance to meet business owners who don't have technical skills but have many problems that can be solved by good data analysts or data scientists. If you can help these business owners understand ways in which data science can be implemented into and useful to their business, you might be able to get a job offer. 😊
